Scaffold Next.js 16 app (TS + Tailwind 4 + App Router + src/)

Initial code scaffolding via create-next-app, integrated with the
existing project docs:

- Next.js 16.2.6, React 19, TypeScript strict, Tailwind 4
- App Router, src/ layout, ESLint configured
- Preserves our README.md, AGENTS.md, OVERVIEW.md (dropped the generic
  ones the scaffolder generated)
- Added .env.example for Supabase keys; gitignore allows it through
- AGENTS.md updated to reflect actual scaffolded stack and absorbs
  the Next.js framework warning block from the scaffolder
- README.md Quick Start filled in with install/dev commands

Next up: Supabase client wiring (browser + server + middleware) and
the magic-link sign-in flow with @HDSecurity.Systems domain check.

Note: npm audit reports a moderate postcss vuln nested inside
Next.js itself; the suggested "fix" would downgrade Next.js to v9.
Ignoring; will resolve when Next.js bumps their bundled postcss.

